<% content_for :title, t(".title") %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="bg-container border border-primary rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-10 shadow-sm">

    <%# Header %>
    <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-primary">
      <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Kenya Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-4">Chancen Companion Mobile App</p>
      <dl class="text-sm text-subdued space-y-1">
        <div><dt class="inline font-medium text-primary">Entity:</dt> <dd class="inline">Chancen International Services</dd></div>
        <div><dt class="inline font-medium text-primary">Effective Date:</dt> <dd class="inline">13.04.2026</dd></div>
        <div><dt class="inline font-medium text-primary">Last Updated:</dt> <dd class="inline">09.04.2026</dd></div>
        <div><dt class="inline font-medium text-primary">Review Cycle:</dt> <dd class="inline">Annual (or earlier if required)</dd></div>
        <div><dt class="inline font-medium text-primary">Next Review Due:</dt> <dd class="inline">13.04.2027</dd></div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-sm sm:prose max-w-none text-primary space-y-8">

      <%# Intro %>
      <section>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">This Privacy Policy explains how personal data relating to <strong>users located in Kenya</strong> is collected, used, disclosed and protected when you use the <strong>Chancen Companion mobile application</strong> (the "App").</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">This Policy is issued in compliance with the Data Protection Act and applicable guidance issued by the Office of the Data Protection Office Commissioner (ODPC).</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">This document <strong>supplements the Chancen Companion Master Privacy Policy.</strong> In the event of any conflict, this <strong>Kenya Privacy Policy Supplement</strong> shall prevail for users located in Kenya.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 1 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">1. About the Chancen Companion App</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">"<strong>Chancen Companion</strong>" refers to the mobile application operated by Chancen that allows users to access program information, including <strong>Income Share Agreement (ISA) participation details</strong>, communications, career resources, and financial literacy tools.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">The App supports students and graduates participating in Chancen education financing programs and related initiatives.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 2 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">2. Local Data Controller</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">For users located in Kenya, the <strong>data controller responsible for your personal data is</strong>:</p>
        <div class="bg-secondary rounded-lg p-4 mb-3 text-sm text-subdued">
          <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-1">Chancen Kenya Ltd</p>
          <p>Company Registration Number: CLG-ABFDBQ</p>
          <p>Registered Address: Jasmine Centre, Westlands</p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:companion@chancen.international" class="text-accent hover:underline">companion@chancen.international</a></p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">As the <strong>Data Controller</strong>, Chancen Kenya Ltd determines how and why your personal data is processed when you use the Chancen Companion App in Kenya.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">The technical infrastructure supporting the App may be operated by:</p>
        <div class="bg-secondary rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-subdued">
          <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-1">Chancen International Services</p>
          <p>Registered in England and Wales</p>
          <p>Company Number: 15299562</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-subdued mt-3">Chancen International Services provides the technology platform and infrastructure that operates the App. However, Chancen Kenya Ltd remains responsible for personal data relating to users located in Kenya.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 3 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">3. ODPC Registration</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen Kenya Ltd is registered with the <strong>Office of the Data Protection Commissioner (ODPC)</strong> as a Data Controller and/or Data Processor under the Kenya Data Protection Act.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">ODPC Registration Number: 147-4900-2C8C</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 4 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">4. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-4">We may collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Identity Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Full name</li>
          <li>Identification or student identification details</li>
          <li>Date of birth (where required)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Contact Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Email address</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Account Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Username and login credentials</li>
          <li>Account activity within the App</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">ISA Program Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>ISA participation status</li>
          <li>Repayment obligations</li>
          <li>Payment history</li>
          <li>Balance estimates</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Device and Technical Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li>Device type</li>
          <li>Operating system</li>
          <li>App usage data</li>
          <li>Log information</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Communications Data</h3>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">When you contact support, provide feedback, or interact with the App's AI chatbot, we may collect the information you share in those communications. This includes messages, questions, and responses exchanged with the chatbot. These interactions help us respond to support requests, improve the accuracy and usefulness of the chatbot, and strengthen our financial literacy tools. Where possible, we anonymise or remove identifying information from these interactions before using them for analysis or product improvement, in order to protect user privacy.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Messages exchanged with Chancen through the App — this includes interactions with an AI chatbot. This helps the AI provide better answers and helps us improve our financial literacy tools. We anonymise users' data to protect their privacy.</li>
          <li>Support requests or feedback</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued">Chancen collects <strong>only the personal data necessary</strong> to provide the App and support participation in Chancen programs.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 5 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">5. Lawful Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">We process personal data on the following legal bases:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Contractual necessity</strong> – to provide App services and manage ISA participation;</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> – to comply with applicable laws and regulatory requirements;</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> – to improve App functionality, security and user experience;</li>
          <li><strong>Consent</strong> – where required, including for specific communications or optional features.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 6 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">6. How We Use Personal Data</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Your personal data may be used for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>Providing access to the Chancen Companion App</li>
          <li>Displaying ISA participation and repayment information</li>
          <li>Managing user accounts</li>
          <li>Communicating program updates and notifications</li>
          <li>Providing career, employment, and financial literacy resources</li>
          <li>Maintaining platform security and preventing fraud</li>
          <li>Improving App functionality and user experience</li>
          <li>Complying with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 7 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">7. ISA Account Data</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">The Chancen Companion App allows users to view information relating to their <strong>Income Share Agreement (ISA)</strong> participation.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">This may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Estimated ISA balance</li>
          <li>Payment history</li>
          <li>Repayment status</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">This information is derived from Chancen's internal systems, including its <strong>Data Warehouse</strong>, which stores program and repayment information.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3"><strong>Balance information displayed in the App may not always reflect real-time updates and should be treated as an informational estimate only.</strong></p>
        <p class="text-subdued">The official record of ISA obligations is maintained by <strong>Chancen Kenya Ltd</strong>. Users who require official balance confirmations should contact Chancen Kenya directly.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 8 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">8. Data Sharing and Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Personal data may be shared with trusted third parties where necessary to operate the App and deliver Chancen services.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">These may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Cloud infrastructure providers</li>
          <li>Technology service providers supporting the App</li>
          <li>Payment processing partners (where applicable)</li>
          <li>Legal or regulatory authorities where required by law</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3"><strong>AI Technology Partners:</strong> We use trusted partners like OpenAI to process your chatbot questions. We take steps to remove your name and ID before sharing this data with the partner, so they can generate a response, but they cannot identify you.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">We do not sell your information to these partners.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">These providers are required to process personal data in accordance with appropriate <strong>security and confidentiality obligations</strong>.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 9 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">9. Data Transfers Outside Kenya</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">To operate the Chancen Companion App, some personal data may be processed or stored outside Kenya.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">For example, technical infrastructure or support services may be provided by <strong>Chancen International Services in the United Kingdom or by international technology providers</strong>.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Where cross-border transfers occur, Chancen implements <strong>appropriate safeguards</strong> to ensure that personal data remains protected in accordance with the <strong>Kenya Data Protection Act, 2019</strong>.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-2">These safeguards may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>contractual data protection obligations with service providers</li>
          <li>secure cloud infrastructure and encryption</li>
          <li>technical and organizational security measures</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 10 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">10. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen takes reasonable <strong>administrative, technical, and physical measures</strong> to protect personal data from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or disclosure.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-2">Security measures may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>encryption of sensitive data</li>
          <li>restricted access controls</li>
          <li>secure infrastructure and monitoring systems</li>
          <li>internal policies governing data protection</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 11 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">11. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>provide App services</li>
          <li>support ISA program participation</li>
          <li>comply with legal or regulatory obligations</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued">Retention periods may vary depending on the nature of the data and applicable legal requirements. However, should the user choose to delete their account through the App settings, we will delete their App-related personal data within 30 (thirty) days unless retention is required by law.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 12 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">12. Your Rights Under the Kenya Data Protection Act</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Under <strong>Section 26 of the Kenya Data Protection Act, 2019</strong>, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Be informed about the use of your personal data;</li>
          <li>Access your personal data;</li>
          <li>Object to the processing of your data;</li>
          <li>Request correction of false or misleading personal data;</li>
          <li>Request deletion of false or misleading personal data;</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent;</li>
          <li><strong>Human Review:</strong> The right to ask for a human to review any important Chancen ISA-related information generated by our AI chatbot.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued">Chancen Kenya Ltd respects these rights and has procedures in place to help users exercise them.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 13 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">13. How to Exercise Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">To exercise your data protection rights, please contact Chancen Kenya Ltd using the contact details provided below.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Requests should include enough information for us to verify your identity and locate your data.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">Chancen Kenya Ltd will aim to respond to requests <strong>within 30 days</strong>, subject to verification and the complexity of the request.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 14 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">14. How to Complain</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">If you are not satisfied with how Chancen Kenya Ltd handles your personal data, you may file a complaint with the <strong>Office of the Data Protection Commissioner (ODPC)</strong>.</p>
        <div class="bg-secondary rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-subdued">
          <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-1">Office of the Data Protection Commissioner (ODPC)</p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://www.odpc.go.ke" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:underline">www.odpc.go.ke</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <%# Section 15 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">15. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology, legal requirements, or App functionality.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Updated versions will be made available within the App.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">Continued use of the App after any updates to this Privacy Policy are published constitutes acceptance of those updates. Where the changes are material, we will notify you through the App or via email, and your continued use of the App following such notification shall constitute your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 16 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">16. Contact Information</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how your personal data is processed, please contact:</p>
        <div class="bg-secondary rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-subdued">
          <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-1">Chancen Kenya Ltd</p>
          <p>Address: Jasmine Centre, Westlands</p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:companion@chancen.international" class="text-accent hover:underline">companion@chancen.international</a></p>
          <p>Phone: +254 718 555585</p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>
